{
  "stem": "2966.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Everyone had to get undressed, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] go over to the edge of that grave, and they were shot.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We know about it almost immediately because-- because it happened in town.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And at that time, we still had Jewish police, which was working with the-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] for the Germans, I would say, or for the committee-- Jewish committee.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were ordered to form a Jewish police, which were coordinating things with the Germans.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Some of our Jewish policeman, truthfully, behaved very badly.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They used to be as bad as-- almost as the Germans, except they had no arms.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They just had a whip or a nightstick, whatever you want to call it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they used to-- Jews were very ingenious.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They used to build things-- false walls in houses, false basements, and things to hide in.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And our Jewish policemen, in many instances, used to know about it because they lived with the Jews and they heard about things.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They heard where their families used to hide.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they used to uncover these things and take people out, just trying to survive themselves.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Unfortunately, very few of them survived, or fortunately.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Because many of them were very bad people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I'll tell you a story about some of them on the end of our concentration camp stories.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But right now, where my mother was shot, then they liquidated the ghetto and my part of town, where we were.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That means that, after they took away the 600 people, and they took-- a lot of people die out from hunger, and there was no need for them to keep the Jews in two places.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
